caption: From the first moment  you come to this restaurant  the personel give you a pleasant feeling. Very congenial stuff, it is a kind restaurant to hang out with buddies or with your date. yummy  food, experienced  chef de cuisine, decent  price and courteous  service. Highly recommended.
Love the tacos and service by bartender!
Great backyard space! Love the spam taco!
The best!  Food, service, atmosphere!  What else could you be looking for?!  Enjoy/Cheers.
Great spot with a cute back patio. Creative frozen drinks and solid food menu. Friendly bar tenders make this a favorite neighborhood haunt.

Dope spot. The tacos are delicious, and they respect a strong drink.  I'll be back here to try their whole taco selection.  Great atmosphere and sensible seating to honor social distancing. Get there before is too cold to sit in their secluded patio space.
Finest food, very kind staff members, constantly good vibes. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is fantastic. Fantastic work.

This is surely one of the best place in the region. Anytime I come to this place I am highly pleased. They preserve their very high  standard service and the topmost level of meals  they provide. You definitely will enjoy this this place. Highly  recommended.
One of my main places to grab something to eat. very good location, clean, and very good customer service. Very good job!
Solid beer options. Nachos were salty. The spam taco is a must-get guilty pleasure. Nice outdoor/backyard space too! Instant go-to for the area.

Super comfy, cozy, pseudo-dive bar. Really comfortable vibe. Staff here are super friendly and I often saw them chatting with people at the bar.  I didn't drink here, but got food and it was pretty good!
Great happy hour
Certainly a place worth trying, the food is fantastic and fresh, the pricing is reasonable and it is consistently neat here. Kudos.

I arrive at this outstanding restaurant every couple of days  as I enjoy the ambiance that is part of this place. The team is highly cordial and well trained. The service is certainly quick. Most important, the food they serve is perfect. I have been there many times and I was always pleased. The payment is fair. I highly recommend this restaurant to to all.
Great cozy spot
Love the tacos and empanadas!!!!

Came here on a Friday night. It was lively but not too crowded. The servers/bartenders were really friendly; the beer selection is great; there are games you can play; and the tacos are delicious. My one qualm was that the food took a loooong time to come out (and we only got 3 tacos). Other than that, would have rated it 5 stars.
Good tacos
A great place to visit!

A very clean place with some great drink deals. I recommend getting a pitcher to split for the value. The breakfast tacos are really good and the atmosphere is nice, including a covered and heated backyard area
Nice cozy place. Food wasn't half bad either.
The decor is kinda corny, but the drinks and food are good.
(Translated by Google) Good selection of beers  (Original) Gute Auswahl an Bieren
Their taco is great!:))
Killer food. Great service. Very Swell.
Decor is confused and the food is meh. Plus the patio is basically inside (so no smoking).
Best spot to grab something when in a rush. The service is efficient, rates are fair, excellent character. Will come back again

If you want an authentic Island taste combined with a new age twist in NYC, you have to come eat at Swell Dive. Filipino Tacos, good drink menu, awesome laidback vibe, all make for a fun atmosphere with friends and delicious food. Check this one out, for sure.
The tacos have a pineapple kick that plays well with the spice. Fantastic. Will come back.
Chill vibe, great tacos.
Awesome cosy spot. Great tacos!
Awesome and flavorful food, I liked the character this spot has, and the staff members were super nice. I will definitely eat here again.
The bartender Mayra is amazing!
Tacos are good, I can taste the Filipino flavor on the tacos,has board games too. Ube rum is so good.

I have a high standard for breakfast tacos. They used too small of tortillas and the flavor just wasn't there. Also the OJ was $4! Too bad. I had heard this place was owned by the same people that owned the kolache place across the street, and that they were both from Austin. If that's true, they have forgotten their taco roots
Great Filipino tacos and a cool spot. Nice little backyard and super friendly staff. The SPAM tacos are 🔥.
This place is worth a try. They serve large portions for affordable prices. Consistently neat and with fantastic mood. Highly recommended.

The taco's are out of this world tasty!! I had the chicken adobo as well as the fish taco. I would highly recommend both. All staff was friendly, polite and attentive. Beers were reasonably priced. Good happy hour too! I will be back!
Noah is very sweet and was super helpful during my visit. Food is out of this world and unique. Filipino breakfast tacos are my new favorite obsession.
Those tacos 🥰
Great ambience, the heated patio was really nice and the fried spam tacos were a revelation.
Pretty good Filipino style tacos! Beer selection is also good! Fun place to hangout with friends!
Really great tacos! There are boards games at the back
Everybody does the mingas but the other stuff is tight too. Sit outside and avoid the chokepoint of the bar and the four tops.
Great food, great bartender, great beer
Tacos tacos tacos they have delish tacos
You can search high and low, but you will never find a nicer smelling bathroom.
Nice laid-back atmosphere. Friendly crowd. Easygoing staff. Racial tension nil. Liked the tacos.
Yumm!
Delicious Filipino inspired tacos!

Best tacos (I know they are fusion but they are still amazing) in Bedstuy. Love the surf vibes as well. Good place to come during the week to watch sports as it doesn't get too busy. Prices for drinks can get steep but otherwise no issues here. A great bar/restaurant!!

Where could you have tacos for breakfast in Brooklyn? Am I in Texas or what? They have a huge cup for your coffee. Their bloody Mary is fantastic. The music in the background is very accommodating, too.
Fun place to visit
Get both veggie tacos. Get beer. Tip well.
Oksy, good to go

I love this place. They have delicious food and good drink options. The best part is the vibe though. The Filipino/island thing really feels fun and genuine, not just kitschy. They offer drink specials and have games as well.
Love this spot! Great tacos and cocktails!
Cheap and tasty
Such a great atmosphere, and that queso!
A longtime neighborhood favorite will be back soon great service great drinks and snacks
Cool vibe and Caitlyn the bartender was really friendly!!!
This place is okay. I've never brought anything. I was just an delivery guy. I pick up and delivery to customer of Postmates
not very big, they do serve pitchers and reasonable prices, may adobo taco was too salty (they over did it with the soy sauce), the nachos were good and the spam taco was also good.

I loved all of their tacos, the service was great and quick and they also have a great selection of beers at a reasonable price. Looking forward to spending time in their huge patio in the summer and trying out some more of their bites! Will definitely return and bring back some more friends along.
Fried. Spam. Tacos.
Horrible smell  nice little spot but nah. Better off going across the street to black swan
Cozy
The tacos tasted really good. Tanduay oh my is a great drink. It’s a nice hang out spot.
Amazing tacos! Definitely try the Filipino varieties!
This place is great and has super good tacos
The Filipino tacos are to die for

I’ve only been here once but had a great time. I love that they have decks of cards and board games. Good beer selection. Will definitely be back to try the food.  Update: I tried the pork taco and it was amazing. I also shared the fishbowl with my girlfriend and it was STRONG.
It's a cozy place that has a good beer selection. The tacos are pretty good.
Great eats and great drinks in a fun environment and outstanding service.
Small venue with a good vibe. I enjoyed my hurricane fries and my cold San miguel beer. Will try their brunch soon.
Amazing margaritas and delicious tacos!
Brooklyn's best bartenders. Tip big.
Good vibe
Exceptional tacos, chilled-out staff, totally relaxed but also perky vibes. A winner
Came here for breakfast after reading reviews. Didn't disappoint. Tacos were SOOOOO tasty. Glad we came. Will come again.
Love this place! Such a cool hangout spot and the breakfast tacos might he the best I've had. Great way to start a date or Meetup with friends

Came in once, and keep going back! Its additive, and soooo good. Chips n queso is to die for, and the tacos are bomb! They have a nice twist on tacos and the flavors are on point. Breakfast tacos are a hidden gem. I Highly recommend them!!!! no table service which is fine with me, so if you are the entitled type, just swallow your pride and go order and pay at the bar like everybody else.
Get the hurricane fries. So good.
as a californian - happy to find INCREDIBLE tacos. haven’t been able to say that since i moved here in 2010.
The best tacos in the city. Whenever I'm in Brooklyn, I will go miles out of my way to come to Swell Dive.

Extremely UNDERWHELMED yes it was mid day but do you know what if feels like to be starving and finally pick a place and all they have is terrible nachos and weak drinks for $16 bucks. I left a $20 after I ate on the table and the bar tender was like wait....then looked at the table another bar tender secured the money like, i was trying to stiff them. Just another reminder stuck with Espinal....the dominican eatery down the block they never fail me!
good breakfast tacos, but small. awesome outdoor dining space!
Great neighborhood bar with good drinks and great vibe.
Great beer selection and food!

Great place but the service is tooooo slow !!! 3 tacos not on peak time took close to 30 Min!!! Also asked for the  veggie tacos not sure why so slow !! At chillos nearby you get your order within 10 min max when the place is packed. Hope the service will get better because this is such a great venue.
Pretty good food, especially for a dive bar.
A few good craft beers on tap, and a better can selection. Delicious tacos, including a couple of vegetarian ones (the cauliflower's fantastic). #craftbeer #nycbeer #vegetarianfriendly
Nice pub with slightly overpriced but delicious tacos.
Unique tasty tacos.
Great Filipino taco place, the appetizers are good, great prices and cute garden in the back
Amazing! Love the tacos

Went there on a hot summer Tuesday evening. Drinks were cold, games were on the TV, and a few people were playing Guess Who the board game. Oh, there's also a swanky backyard, old school video game system tucked in the corner and great music playing throughout the space. Pro Tip: try their frozen Painkiller 😋
Casual Bar with tacos.  It has an assortment of mixed drinks, beers, and real yummy tacos.  The brisket was awe inspiring and the spam taco was a lot of fun.
Taco yum.
It's the ric flair drip of the taco experience, heavy flavours but undercut with subtleties nahmean still ends up sitting real light on the palette, real right on the palette. Lituation/10
AMAZING tacos!!! Can’t beat the price, quality, or flavors! Incredible homemade tortillas too. So so so good.
Some of the best and most creative tacos you'll ever have.
Perfect little nook with great cocktails.  There food is tasty too.  Try the cauliflower nachos or pulled pork tacos.
My favorite place in a city full of favorites.
Some of the best food in the area. Tiny, so seating can be tough to get. Highly recommend, except when I'm there. Then stay away.
Awesome breakfast tacos
The tacos are pricy but good, the place is small but comfortable. It's say this would be a great spot to grab a bite with friends.
Great hole in the wall bar. Also great tacos 🌮
Best beef tacos on planet Earth.

Ordered a drink while reviewing the menu for food. The drink came in a can so i asked for a pint class. The bartender nodded ok.... 20min later no pint glass and the menu was removed from my hands by the bartender multiple times to complete other orders at the register.... airhead service. Assuming they're baked at work.... wont be back.

(Translated by Google) Extremely spiced food, delicious! Cold beer, beer too! Good music and great appetizers ...  (Original) Comida extremamente temperada, deliciosa! Cerveja geladinha, chopp também! Musica boa e ótimos aperitivos...
The best breakfast tacos I've ever had. The coffee is great. Opens early and has a full bar, it's a must go

Knocked two stars off because they don't make Long Island Iced Teas.   Told me that it'd be 40 dollars worth of liquor.  Every bar should be able to make that drink, and every bar does except this one.   I'd give it two stars for that,  but the food was good,  so I feel like 3 stars is appropriate.
My watering hole. Laid back vibe and great staff. Tacos are fire!!

Amazing hole in the wall taco bar! Their beer selection is very unique, serving lots of island brews, but they have the standards as well. Cannot recommend the tacos enough, each one has a unique taste so be sure to mix up your order. The breakfast tacos couldn’t be a better cure for a hangover and make sure you order the homemade queso on everything! The secret to their food is also their homemade tortillas! So fluffy, so warm, so delicious!
Tacos are so so good, and the happy hour is fantastic
A dive bar just as it is called!!

I can't stop telling friends about this spot. I like tacos in general but I LOVE Swell Dive Tacos! I have never fell in love with a taco before but these are truly the best. The bar is super comfortable with a really nice outdoor area for when it gets warmer. The staff is also super nice.
Cozy bar with AWESOME eats!! And the staff are quite friendly!!
The Filipino style tacos are good
Good tacos! The bar has the sweetest patio.
The queso here is incredible. Tortillas made by hand to order. Breakfast tacos are great.
Love the tacos here! You have to try the spam taco!!
Backyard is cozy and the food ROX! Staff is very attentive and can't beat the price!
Come for the breakfast tacos. Stay for the drinks.
Food is absolutely delicious, bartenders are friendly, and the drink selection is great.
Great beer selection!

Eh. Food was just alright. Not a taste sensation, but an OK taco. Wasn't thrilled with the spiral cut french fry with seasoning and sauce. Pretty expensive considering portion size and lack of table service. Didn't try the drinks but they had a decent selection.
Great local place.  Has the equivalent of a taco truck for a kitchen. Each taco is about $5.  You need at least three for a full meal.
good atx vibes here
cool
Yes! Get one of everything on the menu. Drink every cocktail. This place is so good! Get the huricane fries! Cool atmosphere, there's outdoor seating in the back and they have board games!
Tacos were ridiculously small for $5 a pop. Like no bigger than the palm of my hand. Disappointed with choosing this for a late night dinner.
Great tacos, wings, and staff! Love the patio and the surfing videos!

"Please tell me the kitchens open" "It closes at 12. It does every night" "Really should put that on the website or menu or something" "It is. It's everywhere." OK-- except I checked those and it's nowhere. But seems like a chill bar.
Amazing food, big size delicious drinks. Probably the best tacos I've ever had. Get the Smoked Pork Sisig Taco. You won't regret it.
Delicious tacos, nice beer selection, chill surf videos/vibes, & backyard space
Great food and atmosphere
Yummy food, cool drinks, great beer selection
Cute little venue with excellent food and reasonable drinks. The swell nachos are AMAZING!

This is one of my favorite local spots. it has indoor and outdoor seating, board games and fun surfing videos. The team here is super friendly and offer great service. As a vegetarian, I really enjoy the cheese slab taco and the fried okra taco. They make their own tortillas in house and they are DELICIOUS! They have great happy hour deals until 8 that include food and beverage combos.
Great service, amazing tacos, great vibe 10/10 solid spot!!!
Killer atmosphere, genuine staff, and amazing food. Plus their happy hour specials are good. Can't beat that!
Love this place. The hurricane fries, beef tacos, margaritas and micheladas are so freaking good.

Minus one star for not being open during listed hours on a few occasions, and for inconsistent food prep, but the hurricane fries and chicken fried spam tacos are pretty solid.  Bartenders are friendly in a genuine way and the crowd and scene are fairly relaxed.
The margarita, classic, on the rocks. Made by the owner, Filipino guy with cap, amazing. Best I've had. Food is not so good, but I have cravings for the marg.
Love the Charred Beef Taco,Swell Nachos and  the Hurricane Fries. Haven't tried anything else yet on the menu but I will. Good vibes with games good food and drinks.
Good food relaxing mood.

I travel to Brooklyn from Jersey to satisfy my cravings for the charred beef tacos and chips & queso! Pair that with a great beer, laid-back ambiance and friendly staff and patrons - perfect New York evening!
Love their breakfast tacos and beer selection.
Steak tacos!!! Spam tacos!!!!!!! Amazing. Wings were meh, but the steak and fish and spam tacos are amazing!
Good happy hour specials. Tacos are delicious. Queso and the nachos are killer. Friendly service.
Alex works on Thursday's and is my fave bartender. Food is different but good. Fairly quiet bedstuy spot
I tried the breakfast tacos and they were excellent.
Great unique tasty tacos.  Friendly staff.
Just took down a couple chicken Adobo and Beef tacos. Amazing place overall. Five Stars!
Low energy bar. Workers are nice
Fun atmosphere. Very chill and tasty nachos.

Really fun little place. The smoked pork nachos are out of this world. Has a nice back patio with foosball and darts. I like that they keep the menu small and simple, it's a step above the usual bar food but not an overwhelming volume of choices. Highly recommended.
Perfect neighborhood spot. A+ nachos
Love the queso, charred beef, fried okra and drinks.  Surprisingly good wine 👌🏼👌🏼
Charred beef taco and Coco chi cocktail, so delicious
Surf-themed bar with a small menu of excellent Filipino tacos and queso. Back patio, surf video always playing, bar games, and a smattering of unique cocktails and blended drinks.

Swell Dive is a casual spot serving Filipino flavored tacos and island influenced drinks. I have tried the pork sisig, grilled fish and spam tacos. All good but not crave worthy. There are darts and games to keep you entertained but the lack of draft beers make me less inclined to stay. I wish Swell Dive would commit to be either a bar or a restaurant. The place is set up as a restaurant but the menu is limited. The combo somehow does not work as well as other bar restaurants in the hood, although the back patio is a welcome surprise. Worth a visit.
Cute spot with surf vibe.

The tacos were excellent (very flavorful) but the service needs work. It took 50 minutes to get four tacos with only 3 other people/couples in the restaurant, and the three looking-for-something-to-do employees behind the bar didn't show much contrition. The place is new so I'll amend this if things get better, and yes I'm going to find out because all the tacos are awesome. Don't get a margarita though, it seemed to be missing the Triple Sec.

Thoroughly enjoyed the meal, tacos and the nachos are awesome! I must say the smoked pork tacos should be illegal ( amazing). Fresh green and red sauces at the table. The drinks matched the tacos, divine! I'll be back soon to have at it again. My crew also enjoyed!
Great new place. Tacos and margaritas. What else does one need?
